replies.bodyText:
I'm thinking that if invokeCertHandler raises an exception, we should catch that in the JNI code:
https://github.com/dogtagpki/jss/pull/579/files#diff-a977b6f7e7ac81cab2721a9b5333e64fR357
    ret = (*env)->CallIntMethod(env, sslfd_proxy, certAuthHandlerMethod);
    PR_SetError(ret, 0);
Prior to PR_SetError, check if an exception occurred and set it there instead. Then we can use the constant name instead of the value. Thoughts?

That'll work, but are we going to throw a generic NPE or something more specific? Another option is to get the handler from the proxy, then call handler.check() directly. Something like this but using JNI:
handler = proxy.getHandler();
if (handler == null) {
    PR_SetError(-5994, 0);
} else {
    handler.check(proxy);
}

